.TH "create_pbc" 9 "create_pbc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
create_pbc \- build a pbc for transmission
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u64" create_pbc
.BI "(struct hfi1_pportdata *ppd "  ","
.BI "u64 flags "  ","
.BI "int srate_mbs "  ","
.BI "u32 vl "  ","
.BI "u32 dw_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ppd" 12
info of physical Hfi port
.IP "flags" 12
special case flags or-ed in built pbc
.IP "srate_mbs" 12
static rate
.IP "vl" 12
vl
.IP "dw_len" 12
dword length (header words + data words + pbc words)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create a PBC with the given flags, rate, VL, and length.
.SH "NOTE"
The PBC created will not insert any HCRC - all callers but one are
for verbs, which does not use this PSM feature.  The lone other caller
is for the diagnostic interface which calls this if the user does not
supply their own PBC.
